SIMPLE: wind-break
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wind-break
<hw>Wind"-break`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To break the
wind of; to cause to lose breath; to exhaust.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T would <qex>wind-break</qex> a mule to vie burdens with her.</q>
<rj><qau>Ford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wind-break</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wind-break
<hw>Wind"-break`</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A clump of trees serving for a
protection against the force of wind.</def> <mark>[Local, U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wind-broken</ent>⟦br⟧
